<br>
Warriors are there to <br>
1. Soak up as much damage as they can<br>
2. Keep agro in any way they can at their disposal<br>
3. Get beat on and look good while doing it <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
If you think your damage in a Raid type situation as a warrior is going to make a huge differance. Well your probably wrong. With things like critical blasts and mod rods and huge dot's at caster's disposal nowadays. They are going to far outdamage any of the melee classes. The ONLY reason you are there is to take the damage. Low delay weapons will help you do this.<br>
<br>
<br>
Look into this weapon (Preators Blade of Debility). Its sickeningly easy to obtain if your above lvl 40. Its 8-22 +2str +2sta and proc's (Disempower). Disempower is a low lvl debuff. Throw it in your off hand with somthing like a Lammy, Jade Mace, Sambata war staff.. or similar in your main hand. The proc although unreliable like all proc's are, is a good one for droping you on the hate list. It gets resisted alot but still causes agro when resisted. The ratio isnt as good as a 16-30 weapon. But I garuntee it will help you keep and hold agro alot better than the 16-30.<br>
<br>
